<stack_scopes>
| Scope | Triggered when task touches… |
|---|---|
{{stack_scopes}}

Stack detection is hybrid:
1. Path-based inference from the task scope, current worktree, or sprint plan.
2. Explicit user override always wins (e.g., user says "{{example_override}}" → matching scope, even if no path is touched yet).
3. A task may have multiple stacks (e.g., a feature touching both `backend` and `mobile`); load every matching rule.
</stack_scopes>

<domain_scopes>
Business-domain scopes — an axis ORTHOGONAL to stack scope. A developer can be in
`backend` (stack) AND `Card` (domain) at the same time; both rule sets load together.
The set below is the team-wide taxonomy; which domain(s) YOU work in comes from
`.sumela/local.md` `domains:` (per-developer, untracked).

| Domain | Triggered when task touches… |
|---|---|
{{domain_scopes}}

Domain detection is hybrid and INDEPENDENT of stack scope:
1. Per-developer default — the `domains:` key in `.sumela/local.md` (may list several).
2. Explicit user override always wins (e.g., user says "Card sprint" → `Card`).
3. A task may span multiple domains; load EVERY matching domain rule (union).
4. If a `domains:` value is not present in this taxonomy, the agent warns once and
   skips it (see `sumela-prompt.md` STEP 4) — it never fails bootstrap.
</domain_scopes>

